records.addlTxt:
Defendant in custody.
The State moves to amend the charge in count 1 to intimidate victim, contrary to Section 940.45(3) of the Wisconsin Statutes, a Class G felony.  Motion granted.
NO CONTEST plea entered to the amended charge in count 1 of 15 CF 146, intimidate victim.  Convicted.
The State moves to dismiss and read in count 2 of 15 CF 146, disorderly conduct.  Motion granted.
Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for eighteen (18) months.
Conditions of probation:
1) Undergo a psychological evaluation and follow through with all recommendations;
2) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
3) Maintain absolute sobriety except for lawfully prescribed medications which are taken in prescribed doses;
4) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
5) Maintain fulltime employment, schooling or combination of both;
6) Pay court costs;
7) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
8) provide DNA sample and pay the surcharge.  (if it is determined that the defendant has already submitted to a sample, then the surcharges will not be imposed)
The defendant has credit for 75 days on 15 CF 146 if revoked.
(Per Sgt. Brixius at MTSO, the defendants DNA is already on file.  No sample needed to be submitted and therefore no surcharges will be imposed)
Minutes.
